# Forbidden-pattern list for the pre-commit / commit-msg privacy hooks and for
# scripts/check-secrets.sh.
#
# Copy this to  patterns.local  (gitignored) and fill in YOUR real values, so they
# are enforced locally and can never be committed to a public repo:
#
#   cp .githooks/patterns.local.example .githooks/patterns.local
#   git config core.hooksPath .githooks
#
# One POSIX extended-regex per line. Matching is case-insensitive.
#
# ONLY lines starting with "#" are comments. A trailing comment on a pattern line
# becomes part of the regex and silently disables it. Keep comments on their own line.
#
# Patterns for SHAPES (token formats, private IP ranges, key headers) do NOT
# belong here — they describe a form rather than a value, so they are safe to
# publish and already live in scripts/check-secrets.sh.
#
# Examples — replace with your own:
#
#   my-server-hostname
#   203\.0\.113\.[0-9]+
#   /home/myuser
#   mysurname
#   me@example\.com
#
# A private Discord guild ID you don't want public also belongs here:
#
#   \b123456789012345678\b
